Class FrameOrientation2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.FrameOrientation2D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Orientation2DBasics, Orientation2DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.EpsilonComparable<FrameOrientation2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometricallyComparable<FrameOrientation2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometryObject<FrameOrientation2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Settable<FrameOrientation2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, FixedFrameOrientation2DBasics, FrameChangeable, FrameOrientation2DBasics, FrameOrientation2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder

    public class FrameOrientation2D
extends java.lang.Object
implements FrameOrientation2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometryObject<FrameOrientation2D>
    A FrameOrientation2D represents an orientation in the XY-plane expressed in a given reference frame.

      • epsilonEquals

        public boolean epsilonEquals(FrameOrientation2D other,
                             double epsilon)
        Tests if the yaw angle of this orientation is equal to an epsilon to the yaw of other.

        Note that this method performs number comparison and not an angle comparison, such that: -pi ≠ pi.

        Specified by:
        epsilonEquals in interface us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.EpsilonComparable<FrameOrientation2D>
        Parameters:
        other - the query. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance to use.
        Returns:
        true if the two orientations are equal, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.

      • geometricallyEquals

        public boolean geometricallyEquals(FrameOrientation2D other,
                                   double epsilon)
        Compares this to other to determine if the two orientations are geometrically similar, i.e. the difference in yaw of this and other is less than or equal to epsilon.
        Specified by:
        geometricallyEquals in interface us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometricallyComparable<FrameOrientation2D>
        Parameters:
        other - the orientation to compare to. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance of the comparison.
        Returns:
        true if the two orientations represent the same geometry, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.
